    • Example1: the secret key \(s=3=11_{(2)}\)
    • Example2: the secret key \(s=1=01_{(2)}\)

  • 8: 2-bit quantum teleportation
    • Example1: Transmission data \(\left| x \right\rangle=(\left| 0 \right\rangle + \left| 1 \right\rangle)/\sqrt{2}\) (H gate)
    • Example2: Transmission data \(\left| x \right\rangle=\left| 0 \right\rangle\) (No gate)
    • Example3: Transmission data \(\left| x \right\rangle=\left| 1 \right\rangle\) (X gate)
    • Example4: Transmission data \(\left| x \right\rangle=- \left| 1 \right\rangle\) (X gate, Z gate)
    • Example5: Transmission data \(\left| x \right\rangle=i \left| 1 \right\rangle\) (Y gate)
  • 9: Grover algorithm
    • 9-1: Search method of Grover algorithm
      • (1) Superposition state with equal probability amplitude
      • (2) Marking by phase inversion of search solution
      • (3) Inversion around the mean value of the probability amplitude (diffusion conversion)
    • 9-2: In case of another search solution
      • (1) Search solution \(\left | 0 \right\rangle\)
      • (2) Search solution \(\left | 1 \right\rangle\)
      • (3) Search solution \(\left | 2 \right\rangle\)
